tool_description: RapidAPI's official API that allows you to add or update your API’s definition.
name: OpenAPI Provisioning
title: OpenAPI Provisioning

api_list.name: Create Organization (Environment Admin)
api_list.description: Create a new Organization in your Enterprise Hub. Include the following information in your request to create a new Organization.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://openapi-provisioning.p.rapidapi.com/v1/admin/organizations"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "openapi-provisioning.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())

api_list.name: Get App Analytics
api_list.description:
Get analytics for a specified app. You can specify `from` and `to` in order to fine tune the date range.  
    `resolution` can be set to seconds, minutes, or hours.

required_parameters.name: appId
required_parameters.description: A number associated with a specific App. You can get the API ID by using the "Get All Apps" endpoint.
